aph>\\n\\n    <Heading level={3}>🏞️ ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf</Heading>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      The official Ngorongoro Conservation Area fee schedule. Crater service fees, concession\\n      fees, vehicle fees, and per-person entry charges — the real numbers the safari operator\\n      should be quoting you. This is the document to check against their invoice.\\n    </Paragraph>\\n\\n    <Heading level={3}>🕌 Stone Town photo</Heading>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      {visionText.length > 0 \\n        ? visionText.slice(0, 200) + '…'\\n        : 'A bright courtyard or lightwell in Stone Town — whitewashed walls, arched windows, dark wooden balconies. It captures the texture of the old city beautifully.'}\\n    </Paragraph>\\n\\n    <Heading level={3}>🎙️ Voice note — crater day (Ngorongoro)</Heading>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      Emmanuel was your driver-guide at the crater (not Richard). You bought two Maasai beaded\\n      bracelets for Athina from a lady at the rim — roughly TZS 35,000 (~$25). Emmanuel also\\n      told you there's sometimes a ranger tip of ~TZS 5,000 cash at the gate, separate from\\n      park fees — and you want to ask Richard about that before the safari balance payment.\\n    </Paragraph>\\n\\n    <Divider />\\n\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      <Strong>Here's what I'd propose:</Strong> I'll build you a Tanzania trip app right here in this\\n      project — one place you can open on your phone. It'll have your full itinerary, every cost\\n      from the spreadsheet (so you can see what's paid and what's due), the Ngorongoro fee breakdown\\n      to check against the safari invoice, your Stone Town photo, and the crater-day notes from your\\n      voice memo (bracelets, ranger tip, Emmanuel). Plus I'll create a dedicated knowledge space\\n      for each part — Ngorongoro, Zanzibar, the safari circuit — so any question about park rules,\\n      fees, or what you noted lands somewhere it can actually answer.\\n    </Paragraph>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n